title: Getting errors with 3090
body:
## Expected behavior

I've used this program before, so I know that after naming a model after running 6) train Quick96.bat is supposed to initialize, then bring up a preview box.

## Actual behavior

Initializing models: 100%|###############################################################| 5/5 [00:03<00:00,  1.56it/s]

  File "C:\DEEPFAKE\DeepFaceLab_NVIDIA_RTX3000_series\_internal\python-3.6.8\lib\site-packages\scipy\linalg\lapack.py", line 664, in <module>

ImportError: DLL load failed: The paging file is too small for this operation to complete.

This isn't the only error I've gotten. I've ran the batch file multiple times, and have even gotten tensorflow and numpy import errors, so I don't even know what to do at this point.

## Steps to reproduce

Run the quick96 training .bat on a Zotac 3090, I guess.

## Other relevant information
Windows: Version 10.0.19042 Build 19042
Python 3.6.8
